Title : Prashant Dayal
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}
{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}
'''Prashant Dayal''' is an Indian [[journalist]], who broke the story of [[Death of Soharbuddin Sheikh|Sohrabuddin]] encounter case in November 2006.<ref name=rediff>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/special/spec/20070425.htm|title=The journalist who cracked Gujarat fake encounter case|publisher=rediff.com|accessdate=2007-04-25|work=}}</ref> He currently reports as correspondents for multiple print media organizations, including [[The Times of India]]. He also publishes a column titled 'Jivti Varta'.<ref name=toi>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/toireporter/author-Prashant-Dayal.cms|title=Prashant Dayal:The Times of India reporter|publisher=timesofindia.com|accessdate=2014-03-05|work=}}</ref>

==Early life==
He started working in a garage. When in college, he started driving an autorickshaw at night. In his journalism career, Dayal has switched jobs almost 14 times.<ref name=livemint>{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/VTfB9thld0uwCTz8ii1LPP/Lessons-from-the-Gujarat-Model.html|title=Lessons from the Gujarat Model|publisher=livemint.com|accessdate=2014-03-05|work=}}</ref>

==Career==
He admitted of cultivating a habit of drinking alcohol with police officers to bring out reports from them. He was later charged with sedition by [[Gujarat Police]] in 2008. The charges were later quashed in 2013.<ref name=thehindu>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/06/02/stories/2008060259481200.htm|title=Police Commissioner files case against newspaper|publisher=thehindu.com|accessdate=2008-06-02|work=}}</ref><ref name=ifj>{{cite web|url=http://asiapacific.ifj.org/en/articles/ifj-welcomes-quashing-of-sedition-charges-in-indias-gujarat-state|title=IFJ Welcomes Quashing of Sedition Charges in Indiaâ€™s Gujarat State|publisher=ifj.org|accessdate=2013-04-19|work=}}</ref> His reporting eventually led to the arrest of Gujarat police Deputy Inspector General (Border Range) [[D.G. Vanzara|D G Vanzara]], Rajkumar Pandian, superintendent of police with the [[Intelligence Bureau (India)|Intelligence Bureau]], and M N Dinesh Kumar (Rajasthan police) on the charge of murdering [[Death of Sohrabuddin Sheikh|Sohrabuddin Sheikh]] and other fake encounter's.

